                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.373,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 70259,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 02-819, Kontrick against Ryan will be announced by Justice Ginsburg."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.373,
                        "stop": 355.204,
                        "byte_start": 70259,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.373,
                                "stop": 18.686,
                                "byte_start": 70259,
                                "byte_stop": 103487,
                                "text": "This case, which comes to us from the Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit, involves a question of time."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.686,
                                "stop": 22.722,
                                "byte_start": 103487,
                                "byte_stop": 119578,
                                "text": "The setting is a Chapter 7 bankruptcy proceeding."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.722,
                                "stop": 41.676,
                                "byte_start": 119578,
                                "byte_stop": 195438,
                                "text": "Key to our decision is the distinction between laws determining a court\u0027s subject matter jurisdiction, in other words, laws defining the kinds of cases courts are authorized to hear, and rules of a lesser order governing the processing the claims in court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 41.676,
                                "stop": 52.067,
                                "byte_start": 195438,
                                "byte_stop": 237025,
                                "text": "The underlying controversy involves a bankrupt debtor, Dr. Andrew Kontrick and his principle creditor and former partner in plastic surgery, Dr. Robert Ryan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.067,
                                "stop": 80.983,
                                "byte_start": 237025,
                                "byte_stop": 352695,
                                "text": "Ryan objected to an order that would discharge Kontrick from his debt, in fraud of creditors, Ryan complained, Kontrick had converted a husband-wife joint bank account into an account in his wife\u2019s name only thereafter Kontrick continued to deposit his salary checks into that account and use the funds not to pay creditors but to cover everyday family living expenses."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.983,
                                "stop": 89.425,
                                "byte_start": 352695,
                                "byte_stop": 386445,
                                "text": "Bankruptcy Rule 4004 gives creditors a 60-day period to object to a debtor\u2019s discharge."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.425,
                                "stop": 101.178,
                                "byte_start": 386445,
                                "byte_stop": 433465,
                                "text": "The Rule allows one time extension but only if the creditor asks for the extra time before the initial 60-day period expires."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.178,
                                "stop": 105.85,
                                "byte_start": 433465,
                                "byte_stop": 452169,
                                "text": "Ryan missed the initial 60-days and did not ask for an extension."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.85,
                                "stop": 116.497,
                                "byte_start": 452169,
                                "byte_stop": 494696,
                                "text": "Kontrick, nevertheless, answered Ryan\u2019s claim, litigated the question whether the name change and the bank account defrauded creditors and lost on the merits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.497,
                                "stop": 120.059,
                                "byte_start": 494696,
                                "byte_stop": 509012,
                                "text": "After that loss, Kontrick urged the time bar."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.059,
                                "stop": 136.469,
                                "byte_start": 509012,
                                "byte_stop": 574631,
                                "text": "He said he could do so however late the date because Bankruptcy Rule 4004\u0027s time prescription is jurisdictional and therefore, a matter that could be raised even after an adjudication on the merits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.469,
                                "stop": 147.047,
                                "byte_start": 574631,
                                "byte_stop": 616950,
                                "text": "The courts below held that Rule 4004 is not jurisdictional and therefore, could not be invoked to nullify the decision in Ryan\u2019s favor."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.047,
                                "stop": 157.478,
                                "byte_start": 616950,
                                "byte_stop": 658641,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari because other courts have held that Rule 4004\u0027s time prescription is jurisdictional."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.478,
                                "stop": 162.367,
                                "byte_start": 658641,
                                "byte_stop": 678181,
                                "text": "Rule 4004 we now affirm is not jurisdictional."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.367,
                                "stop": 171.555,
                                "byte_start": 678181,
                                "byte_stop": 714961,
                                "text": "The subject matter jurisdiction of Federal Courts, the cases those courts can hear and decide maybe prescribed only by Congress."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 171.555,
                                "stop": 179.469,
                                "byte_start": 714961,
                                "byte_stop": 746621,
                                "text": "Congress prescribed that objections to discharges fall within the Bankruptcy Court\u2019s subject matter jurisdiction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.469,
                                "stop": 191.47,
                                "byte_start": 746621,
                                "byte_stop": 794582,
                                "text": "Congress built no time constraint into that statutory authorization, instead the time limit\u2019s relevant here are contained in rules and procedure for Bankruptcy Courts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 191.47,
                                "stop": 196.985,
                                "byte_start": 794582,
                                "byte_stop": 816630,
                                "text": "Those rules do not delineate what cases Bankruptcy Courts are competent to adjudicate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 196.985,
                                "stop": 200.056,
                                "byte_start": 816630,
                                "byte_stop": 828959,
                                "text": "They are simply plain processing rules."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 200.056,
                                "stop": 214.483,
                                "byte_start": 828959,
                                "byte_stop": 886638,
                                "text": "In arguing that Rule 4004 should have the same practical effect as a statutory provision governing subject matter jurisdiction contract overlooks this critical difference."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 214.483,
                                "stop": 236.903,
                                "byte_start": 886638,
                                "byte_stop": 976290,
                                "text": "Characteristically, a court\u2019s subject matter jurisdiction cannot be enlarged to account for the party\u2019s litigation conduct, but a claim processing rule even strict one like Bankruptcy Rule 4004 can be forfeited if the body invoking the rule waits too long to raise a point."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 236.903,
                                "stop": 253.633,
                                "byte_start": 976290,
                                "byte_stop": 1043268,
                                "text": "No reasonable construction of complaint processing Bankruptcy Rule 4004 would allow a litigant, in debtor Kontrick\u0027s shoes, to defeat a claim as filed too late after the litigant has lost on the merits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 253.633,
                                "stop": 263.791,
                                "byte_start": 1043268,
                                "byte_stop": 1083914,
                                "text": "A prime purpose of the rule is to afford the bankrupt debtor and affirmative defense to a complaint untimely filed by a creditor."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 263.791,
                                "stop": 268.246,
                                "byte_start": 1083914,
                                "byte_stop": 1101678,
                                "text": "Kontrick raised no such defense when he answered Ryan\u2019s complaint."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 268.246,
                                "stop": 282.764,
                                "byte_start": 1101678,
                                "byte_stop": 1159774,
                                "text": "Kontrick additionally argues that Rule 4004\u2019s time constraint is so tight, it allows no recourse to equitable exceptions but Ryan never maintained that he qualified for an equitable exception."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 282.764,
                                "stop": 290.434,
                                "byte_start": 1159774,
                                "byte_stop": 1190494,
                                "text": "Therefore, we do not address the question whether Rule 4004 accommodates equitable exceptions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 290.434,
                                "stop": 294.683,
                                "byte_start": 1190494,
                                "byte_stop": 1207421,
                                "text": "The sole question we decide is one of forfeiter."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 294.683,
                                "stop": 303.556,
                                "byte_start": 1207421,
                                "byte_stop": 1242948,
                                "text": "Under the governing claim processing rules, the defense is lost if it is not included in the complaint or in an amended answer."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 303.556,
                                "stop": 310.241,
                                "byte_start": 1242948,
                                "byte_stop": 1269697,
                                "text": "Only a subject matter jurisdiction objection lingers on beyond the pleading stage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 310.241,
                                "stop": 317.737,
                                "byte_start": 1269697,
                                "byte_stop": 1299686,
                                "text": "Kontrick\u0027s post-adjudication assertion that Ryan\u2019s claim was untimely is not of that extraordinary order."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 317.737,
                                "stop": 336.447,
                                "byte_start": 1299686,
                                "byte_stop": 1374501,
                                "text": "In sum, affirming the judgment of the Court of Appeals, we hold that a debtor forfeits the right to rely on Rule 4004 if the debtor does not raise the rule\u0027s time limitation before the Bankruptcy Court reaches the merits of the creditor\u2019s objection to discharge."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 336.447,
                                "stop": 355.204,
                                "byte_start": 1374501,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Court\u2019s decision is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
